                <h4>Complementary Courses (12 credits)</h4>

    
              <p>12 credits selected as follows:</p>
<p>- At least 6 of the 12 credits have to be at the 400 or 500 level.</p>
<p>- At least 6 of the 400- or 500-level credits have to be from outside the student's home department.</p>
    
      
      
                <h4></h4>

    
              <p>0-6 credits from the following list of 200- and 300-level courses:</p>
<p>Notes:<br />
* Students may select <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/anat-212">ANAT 212</a> or <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/bioc-212">BIOC 212</a> or <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/biol-201">BIOL 201</a>.</p>
<p>** Students may select either <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/biol-306">BIOL 306</a> or <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/phgy-314">PHGY 314</a>.</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
