                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/psyc-501" class="program-course-title">
              PSYC 501 Auditory Perception (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-34475" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Psychology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Psychology              : Auditory perception and its neural correlates, covering acoustics, auditory anatomy and neurobiology, and the neural correlates of perception of loudness, pitch, spatial location, frequency specificity, musical, speech sounds, and segregation of component sounds in multi-sound environments in both humans and animals.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
